<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[139,1160,621,921]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
Rare herbivorous ladybird. A reduction of the membraneous wings is probably a reason for its low dispersal ability and local (although sometimes relatively abundant) occurrence. In the Baltic Coast (only in the eastern part) recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="BARTOSZYNSKI A." box="[694,913,682,706]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" pagination="69 - 80" refId="ref6727" refString="BARTOSZYNSKI A. 1937. Coleopterologische Studien an der Polnischen Ostseekuste. Fortsetzung der Erforschung der Kaferfauna der Halbinsel Hel. Fragmenta Faunistica Musei Zoologici Polonici 3: 69 - 80. [In Polish with German summary]" type="journal article" year="1937">Bartoszyński (1937)</bibRefCitation>
in Puck, by 
<bibRefCitation author="BIELAWSKI R." pageId="9" pageNumber="48" pagination="191 - 205" refId="ref6898" refString="BIELAWSKI R. 1962. Materialien zur Kenntnis der Coccinellidae Polens. I (Coleoptera). Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne / Bulletin Entomologique de Pologne 32: 191 - 205. [In Polish]" type="journal article" year="1962">Bielawski (1962)</bibRefCitation>
in Elbląg and Tolkmicko, and recently by 
<bibRefCitation author="NAPIONTEK M. &amp; SZAWARYN K." box="[698,1038,713,737]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 2" refId="ref8814" refString="NAPIONTEK M. &amp; SZAWARYN K. 2017. Confirmation of the occurrence of Cynegetis impunctata (LINNAEUS, 1767) (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae) in Pomerania. Acta entomologica silesiana 25: 1 - 2. [In Polish]" type="journal article" year="2017">Napiontek &amp; Szawaryn (2017)</bibRefCitation>
in Gdańsk Oliwa. The specimens collected in this study confirm the existence of a stable population of 
<emphasis box="[139,291,775,798]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">C. impunctata</emphasis>
in the investigated area. Other recent data from 
<collectingCountry box="[851,925,774,798]" name="Poland" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Poland</collectingCountry>
refer to localities in the Pomeranian Lake District (
<bibRefCitation author="CERYNGIER P. &amp; ROMANOWSKI J. &amp; ROMANOWSKI M." box="[468,714,805,829]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" pagination="41 - 58" refId="ref7465" refString="CERYNGIER P., ROMANOWSKI J. &amp; ROMANOWSKI M. 2016 b. Ladybird beetles (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae) of Cedynia Landscape Park. Wiadomosci Entomologiczne 35: 41 - 58. [In Polish with English abstract]" type="journal article" year="2016">Ceryngier et al. 2016b</bibRefCitation>
), Masurian Lake District (Bubienko et al. 2010), Wielkopolska-Kujawy Lowland (
<bibRefCitation author="RUTA R." box="[591,713,836,860]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" pagination="49 - 106" refId="ref9154" refString="RUTA R. 2006. Chrzaszcze (Insecta: Coleoptera) kserotermicznych Wzgorz Byszewickich w Dolinie Noteci. Nowy Pamietnik Fizjograficzny 5 (1 - 2): 49 - 106." type="journal article" year="2006">Ruta 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="RENNER K. &amp; MESSUTAT J." box="[731,1020,836,860]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" pagination="16 - 20" refId="ref9093" refString="RENNER K. &amp; MESSUTAT J. 2007. Untersuchungen zur Kaferfauna der Umgebung von Skwierzyna im westlichen Polen (Wielkopolska). Coleo 8: 16 - 20." type="journal article" year="2007">Renner &amp; Messutat 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="RUTA R. &amp; JALOSZYNSKI P. &amp; KONWERSKI S. &amp; MAJEWSKI T. &amp; BARLOZEK T." pageId="9" pageNumber="48" pagination="91 - 112" refId="ref9186" refString="RUTA R., JALOSZYNSKI P., KONWERSKI S., MAJEWSKI T. &amp; BARLOZEK T. 2009. Ladybird beetles (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae) of Poland. Part 1. New faunistic data. Wiadomosci Entomologiczne 28: 91 - 112. [In Polish with English abstract]." type="journal article" year="2009">Ruta et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingRegion box="[221,373,866,890]" country="Poland" name="Dolnoslaskie" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Lower Silesia</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="GREN C. &amp; SZOLTYS H. &amp; GRZYWOCZ J. &amp; KROLIK R." box="[392,587,866,890]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" pagination="31 - 52" refId="ref7933" refString="GREN C., SZOLTYS H., GRZYWOCZ J. &amp; KROLIK R. 2013. Beetles (Coleoptera) of the Lower and Upper Silesia - the current state of knowledge and new faunistic data: ladybird beetles (Coccinellidae). Acta entomologica silesiana 21: 31 - 52. [In Polish with English abstract]" type="journal article" year="2013">Greń et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
), Trzebnickie Hills (
<bibRefCitation author="RUTA R. &amp; JALOSZYNSKI P. &amp; KONWERSKI S. &amp; MAJEWSKI T. &amp; BARLOZEK T." box="[821,1010,866,890]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" pagination="91 - 112" refId="ref9186" refString="RUTA R., JALOSZYNSKI P., KONWERSKI S., MAJEWSKI T. &amp; BARLOZEK T. 2009. Ladybird beetles (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae) of Poland. Part 1. New faunistic data. Wiadomosci Entomologiczne 28: 91 - 112. [In Polish with English abstract]." type="journal article" year="2009">Ruta et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and Eastern Sudety Mts (
<bibRefCitation author="RUTA R. &amp; JALOSZYNSKI P. &amp; KONWERSKI S. &amp; MAJEWSKI T. &amp; BARLOZEK T." box="[275,451,897,921]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" pagination="91 - 112" refId="ref9186" refString="RUTA R., JALOSZYNSKI P., KONWERSKI S., MAJEWSKI T. &amp; BARLOZEK T. 2009. Ladybird beetles (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae) of Poland. Part 1. New faunistic data. Wiadomosci Entomologiczne 28: 91 - 112. [In Polish with English abstract]." type="journal article" year="2009">Ruta et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
